<p>Well, it suddenly feels like summer. Bloody warm. If it hadn't been for a few thin clouds fighting off the sun, Greg and I would've cooked on upper Poorman. (Personally, I can't wait until fall.) Other than the muggy weather, it was a great ride today. Poorman is fairly passable, i.e., packed down and clean, right now.</p>
<h6>Morning Post</h6>
<blockquote><div class="center"><a href="http://www.flagstafffrenzy.org/wp-content/uploads/2008/05/welding-daves-bike.jpg"><img src="http://www.flagstafffrenzy.org/wp-content/uploads/2008/05/welding-daves-bike.jpg" width="400" /></a><br />Dr. Underwood taking a page from Frankenstein.</div>
<p>Fantastic weather has returned and so has Dave's surgically altered bike. We're thinking a good test would be the cobbles of Poorman Road. If you want to join us, meet up in front of Telecom at high noon, but please, leave your welding torches and other <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fhz6i6JGzIU">incendiary devices</a> at home.</p>
</blockquote>